identifications.body: By currently recognised species barriers A. hentzi is the only theraphosid species to occur in OK. There were formerly two others - A. odelli and A. baergi (the latter was actually a misidentified Brachypelma sp. from Mexico incorrectly labelled as coming from Fayetteville, AK) but A. odelli was found to be a synonym of A. hentzi - the former justification for its separation by Smith (1994) was predominately spermathecae morphology which is quite variable in intraspecific samples of US Aphonopelma species.
